<section class="pt-24 pb-12">
  <%# IndieWeb identity: hidden h-card so webmention/mf2 parsers can resolve
      the site's author from the homepage (mirrors the one on /about/). %>
  <div class="h-card hidden">
    <a class="u-url p-name" href="https://andrewm.codes/">Andrew Mason</a>
    <img class="u-photo" src="/images/main-avatar.png" alt="">
  </div>
  <h1 class="<%= h1_class %> m-0 mb-8">
    Andrew Mason<span class="text-mint-11">.</span>
  </h1>
  <%= render Text.new(variant: :lead, class: "m-0 mb-4") do %>
    Ruby on Rails engineer at
    <%= render Link.new(href: "https://podia.com", variant: :inline) do %>Podia<% end %>, co-host of
    <%= render Link.new(href: "/speaking/", variant: :inline) do %>Remote Ruby<% end %>, and based in Arizona.
  <% end %>
  <%= render Text.new(variant: :lead, class: "m-0 mb-4") do %>
    I spend my time on the parts of Rails that compound — fast CI and test
    suites, developer tooling, and the workflow details that make a team
    quicker. Most of what I learn shipping software for a living ends up
    written down here.
  <% end %>
  <%= render Text.new(variant: :lead, class: "m-0 mb-4") do %>
    You'll find my
    <%= render Link.new(href: "/posts/", variant: :inline) do %>writing<% end %>,
    <%= render Link.new(href: "/projects/", variant: :inline) do %>open source<% end %>, and
    <%= render Link.new(href: "/speaking/", variant: :inline) do %>talks and podcasts<% end %>
    here. Mostly so I can find them again later.
  <% end %>
  <%# Kept as a component-owned margin (mt-8): a one-off gap between prose and the CTA row, not a repeated layout rhythm a parent owns. %>
  <%= render Inline.new(gap: :sm2, class: "mt-8") do %>
    <%= render Button.new(href: "/posts/", variant: :primary, size: :xl) do %>
      Read the writing
      <%= render Icon.new(
        name: "arrow_right",
        class: "ml-1.5 inline-block transition-transform group-hover:translate-x-0.5",
      ) %>
    <% end %>
    <%= render Button.new(href: "/projects/", variant: :secondary, size: :xl) do %>
      Browse projects
    <% end %>
    <%= render Button.new(href: "https://remoteruby.com/", variant: :ghost, size: :xl) do %>
      Listen to Remote Ruby
    <% end %>
  <% end %>
</section>
